arrangement.p:
Series II: Predecessor Companies (1815-1907) focuses almost exclusively on railroads that merged, at various times, into the New York, New Haven & Hartford Railroad.  The collection holds documents related to the following railroads: Boston, Hartford and Erie Railroad; 
Boston and New York Airline Railroad;  Central New England Railway; Charles River Railroad; Chicago and Evanston Railroad; Connecticut River Railroad; Hartford and New Haven Railroad;  Hartford, Providence, and 
Fishkill Railroad ; Housatonic Railroad; Housantonic and Naugatuck Railroad; Meriden and Cromwell Railroad; Meriden, Waterbury, and Connecticut River Railroad; Naugatuck Railroad; New Haven and Derby Railroad; 
New Haven and Northern Railroad; New Haven and Northampton Company; New York and New England Railroad; 
New York and New Haven Railroad; New York, New Haven &  Hartford Railroad; New York, Providence and Boston Railroad; Newburgh, Dutchess and Connecticut Railroad;  Norfolk County Railroad; Philadelphia, Reading, and New England Railroad; Poughkeepsie and Eastern Railway. Documents related to Charles F. Pond can be found in the Hartford and New Haven Railroad folders.
